Ragnar - Class in shellshocker
User-controlled character that has changing attributes. Attributes include location, speed, direction, and information regarding quantities of weapons, health, shield, and bombs.
Ragnar() - Constructor for class shellshocker.Ragnar
Default constructor for the class. Takes in the images of the user-controlled character and sets positional and speed values.
Reactor - Class in shellshocker
Creates a reactor object that, when destroyed, results in the end of the ShellShocker game.
Reactor(int, int, int) - Constructor for class shellshocker.Reactor
Constructor that creates a reactor object that has location and health.
removeEnemies(int, int) - Method in class shellshocker.ControlCentral
Simulates a bomb explosion by dealing damage to all enemy units in a specified range of the blast.
removeProfile() - Static method in class shellshocker.TheGame
Removes the current profile accessed by the user from the list of profiles.
revertXPos() - Method in class shellshocker.Ragnar
Sets the x-coordinate of the position of the character back to the stored x-coordinate value.
revertYPos() - Method in class shellshocker.Ragnar
Sets the y-coordinate of the position of the character back to the stored y-coordinate value.
Rotatable - Interface in shellshocker
Interface that, when implemented, creates methods that relate to rotating objects in the coordinate plane. These objects will have a position, rotation, and dimensions.
rotateImage(double) - Method in class shellshocker.Barrel

rotateImage(double) - Method in class shellshocker.Weapon

run() - Method in class shellshocker.ControlCentral
Used to create a thread, starting the thread causes the run method to be called in that thread. Calls the repaint method of Canvas.
runCredits() - Method in class shellshocker.TheGame
Runs a screen containing the credits for the game.
runLoginPage() - Method in class shellshocker.TheGame
Runs a page containing a login system in which a user enters a username and password in order to access a profile.
runNewUser() - Method in class shellshocker.TheGame
Runs a page that allows users to create new profiles. A username and password are asked to be entered by the user.
runStartPage() - Method in class shellshocker.TheGame
Runs the start page of the menu. The start page will include buttons that provide options to the user for accessing the game along with other information about the game.
runTutorial() - Method in class shellshocker.TheGame
